INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("220", "1", "2015-07-22 16:59:11", "2015-07-22 16:59:11", "Get to NFV faster with an ecosystem of partners The CloudBand Ecosystem Program is an NFV community that was created to  encourage and facilitate the exchange, exploration and collaboration  of service providers, NFV platform partners and  virtual network function vendors to help accelerate NFV  development and implementation.\n\nThe program provides access to the <a href=\"/program/ecosystem-lab\">Cloud Innovation Center (CIC)</a> where there is open access  to the CloudBand NFV Platform and support resource and tools to  onboard applications from Alcatel‐Lucent or other 3rd party VNF’s.  It also provides a central portal for collaboration with other members and access to previously tested use cases and solution ideas to advance the deployment and business case for NFV.\n\nCreated in Oct 2013 and the first NFV Ecosystem launched, it now  has over 60 members: Service Providers, NFV Platform Partners  and Virtual Network Function Vendors. The program is by invitation only.\n\nAlcatel‐Lucent is an ecosystem member and our vIMS, vEPC, and vRAN utilize the CloudBand Innovation Center as a part of the NFV ecosystem. Nuage Networks is also a member of the ecosystem and Nuage Networks VSP is part of the CloudBand NFV Platform. Bell labs consulting services are also aligned with the ecosystem and are equipped to do business modeling and other consulting services triggered by ecosystem member requests.\n\n<strong>Our mission</strong>\nOperators cannot make the transition to virtualization alone. NFV is a complex and challenging process that brings together many new technologies and takes many minds working together to build this new architecture. Many smart and innovative vendors and operators are making significant contributions to specific parts of NFV, which prompted the need to surround us with partners that share our same philosophy.\n\nAlcatel‐Lucent believes in helping service providers get to NFV faster. This means:\n<ul>\n	<li>Join forces to overcome complexity</li>\n	<li>Accelerate maturity of all NFV component</li>\n	<li>Validate VNF Lifecycle management approaches</li>\n	<li>Test the onboarding of many different VNF vendors</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>\nBenefits of joining the program</strong>\nOur program provides a hub, where application providers, platform partners and service \nproviders can share information and collaborate to create innovative NFV proof of concepts. We offer our members the opportunity to:\n<ul>\n	<li>Review use cases and proof points created with our community members</li>\n	<li>Connect to members and explore further mutual areas of interest</li>\n	<li>Participate in specific ecosystem events, round tables, trainings...</li>\n	<li>Get access to CloudBand ’s technical library</li>\n	<li>Bring us application partners and favorite use cases. We will provide access to a dedicated lab environment that includes the full CloudBand solution, as well as training and support to onboard apps onto CloudBand. (This lab is located at the Cloud Innovation Center (CIC) in Naperville, just outside Chicago).</li>\n	<li>Provide guidance and direction to make our Ecosystem offer the most value for your needs</li>\n</ul>\n<a href=\"http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/nfv-lab.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-269\" src=\"http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/nfv-lab.jpg\" alt=\"nfv-lab\" width=\"710\" height=\"325\" /></a>\n\n<strong>On the way to certification</strong>\nThe CloudBand Ecosystem program is not a commercial program. It highlights collaboration but does not indicate endorsement of an application nor any agreement to resell. Any resale agreement that may exist would be created outside of the Ecosystem program.\n\nThe CloudBand Ecosystem program is primarily a collaboration program where we work to help the community understand NFV and how to operate in a cloud environment; it is not a certification program.\n\nParticipation in the program does not guarantee the quality of a VNF nor does it assess or assure the quality of deployment of the VNF into a service provider environment. We are building prototypes and use cases but are not certifying third‐party products or solutions. Moving forward, we will be able to provide more stringent test plans, pre‐ integration levels and deployment templates.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBy working together, the processes of specifying and integrating all the pieces can be faster, accelerating the reality of NFV in the cloud.\nValerie Noto\nDir CloudBand Ecosystem\n@valerienoto\n\n<a href=\"/contact\">Contact Us</a>", "Cloudband Ecosystem Program", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "7-autosave-v1", "", "", "2015-07-22 16:59:11", "2015-07-22 16:59:11", "", "7", "http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/2015/07/22/7-autosave-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
