INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("331", "1", "2014-05-07 18:26:26", "2014-05-07 18:26:26", "<a href=\"http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/IMG_4776-300x225.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-332\" src=\"http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/IMG_4776-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_4776-300x225\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>What a great time with our Ecosystem partners last week in Naperville!\r\n\r\nFor two days, the CloudBand team hosted 30 of our passionate NFV ecosystem members at the CloudBand Innovation Center in Chicago. 14 companies were present : Red Hat, Saisie, JDSU, EXFO, Procera, Larsen &amp; Toubro, Citrix, Radcom, Radware, Metaswitch, Contextream, FusionIO, Sonus and Cellwize.\r\n\r\nThe audience was focused, curious and highly interactive. There was a common thread of openess and eagerness to collaborate.\r\n\r\nIt is so rewarding to have people tell you that the CloudBand Ecosystem is unique in the sense that it provides not only the technical workspace to learn, test, develop, and onboard vNF apps, but it also provides a open forum to generate interactions between companies — for real. This collaboration is now recognized by the industry as a key to progress in the understanding of NFV challenges. In the CloudBand Ecosystem, our partners say they can actually find a forum for open discussion between skilled parties\r\n\r\nSo what was this convention about? Well, more than a training, it was a dialogue. There was a deep-dive into the CloudBand solution, services, architecture, some hands-on recipe writing, many demos, a lab tour…. But more importantly, a venue to discuss NFV opportunities and challenges with peers. We presented our CloudBand road map and got invaluable feedback from the community, providing some comfort that we are heading in the right direction for future development of our NFV platform.\r\n\r\nWe were proud to hear positive comments about our product maturity and it’s multi-platform approach uniqueness both north bound and south bound.\r\n\r\nThis was very rewarding for the CloudBand Ecosystem team to see 9 months of hard work blooming and really creating value to our community now.\r\n\r\nWe are clearly engaged and eager to continue the good work to help Service Providers move to NFV: new use-cases are on the way, new events will be proposed, key initiatives with Intel and Red Hat are under preparation, new partners are joining to enrich discussions even more…. Stay tuned, the jam has started!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/698a40f583be2cc7668e71e5864a8926.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-333\" src=\"http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/698a40f583be2cc7668e71e5864a8926.png\" alt=\"698a40f583be2cc7668e71e5864a8926\" width=\"243\" height=\"256\" /></a>\r\n\r\nValerie", "Where Training Meets Teaming: CloudBand Partners Meeting Recap", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "where-training-meets-teaming-cloudband-partners-meeting-recap", "", "", "2015-07-22 18:26:38", "2015-07-22 18:26:38", "", "0", "http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/?p=331", "0", "post", "", "0");
