make this happen. Yet, this is just the beginning – hold onto your seats to see how the industry will change with NFV.", "Closing Cloud Circles: Thoughts on ALU CEO NFV Announcement", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "343-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-07-22 18:30:48", "2015-07-22 18:30:48", "", "343", "http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/2015/07/22/343-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("345", "1", "2013-07-18 18:31:46", "2013-07-18 18:31:46", "<div class=\"post-content\">\r\n\r\nLast week one of the biggest global service providers came to visit us in Israel. I enjoy these face-to-face meetings. There is nothing more valuable than a healthy round table discussion about obstacles that we are encountering in our industry and possibilities of how to overcome them. One of the first topics raised by our partner was around the importance of a healthy, innovative ecosystem to help drive the NFV transformation and generate value for all of us. I couldn’t agree more.\r\n\r\nAlcatel-Lucent cares about our Service Provider customers; their hurdles are our hurdles. We kept the Service Provider in mind from the onset of building CloudBand ™ over two years ago.Our original founder was the pioneer of telecommunications. We are eager to continue that early spark of innovation that will help service providers once again become leaders and not laagers in this new web dominated world. Over the past two years I have been working on helping leading Service Providers around the globe leverage Cloud to re-build their networks. But that alone is not enough. Our customers can no longer advance by their sheer will power.  They need like-minded partners to help arrive at this journey of NFV.\r\n\r\nThis week we announced the launch of our CloudBand Ecosystem Program ™, one of our contributions to the NFV community to help gain momentum in this area. Our ambition is to build a community of partners (Service Providers, NFV Application Vendors, NFV Solution Partners) that share the common goal of helping operators transform their networks. By working together, we can create an avenue for innovation through collaboration, accelerate development and create new revenue opportunities. Since we launched the program we have received profound support from the industry, saying that our ecosystem is a <a title=\"Testimonials\" href=\"http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/testimonials/\">crucial contribution to the market.</a>\r\n\r\nI believe that Telco’s can become a platform for innovation and services that can scale; but it all comes down to sharing. Taking the best of what each partner has to offer and combining it with other products and services to create new and unique services for the benefit of consumers and businesses. I’m confident that the future of the network will be software driven and open. The days of hiding the network “know how” in a sea of complexity are gone. To drive change quickly, the success of the network is two-fold; it will depend  on cloudifying network functions and collaborating with the growing number of companies that Service Providers can innovate with and the pace at which they can experiment.\r\n\r\nI’m excited about the future, – I welcome you to join the CloudBand Ecosystem Program, and let’s make the journey to NFV faster starting today.\r\n\r\nRoy Amir,\r\nSr. Director Strategy and Partnership of CloudBand Business Unit, Alcatel-Lucent\r\n\r\n</div>", "Today is a great day for the NFV community", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "today-is-a-great-day-for-the-nfv-community", "", "", "2015-07-22 18:32:02", "2015-07-22 18:32:02", "", "0", "http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/?p=345", "0", "post", "", "0");
