ith Bhaskar Gorti, President, IP Platforms Business Group, Alcatel-Lucent</strong></h3>\r\nThe goal with the new technologies, NFV and SDN, is to increase operational efficiency - that gives operators the oxygen to innovate. All the functions Alcatel-Lucent already has live in the network are on a virtualisation and cloudification journey. In this video, Bashkar Ghorti, highlights Alcatel-Lucent vision and strategy in enabling service provider to deploy NFV.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 last\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.telecomtv.com/embed/video/using-nfv-to-reach-the-services-existing-technology-cant-12497/820/?autoplay=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"off\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Using NFV to reach the services existing technology can\'t</strong></h3>\r\nPeter Margaris, Head of Service Provider Product Marketing, F5, outlines the opportunities versus the challenges of NFV, and how the virtualisation technology will particularly affect Layers 4 through 7 of the OSI model. He also lists the benefits of working in close collaboration with Alcatel Lucent and just what Alcatel Lucent\'s end-to-end and open NFV platform and ecosystem, CloudBand, brings to the party.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!--row-->\r\n<div class=\"clearboth\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.telecomtv.com/embed/video/procera-keen-to-turn-into-a-pure-software-vendor-12498/822/?autoplay=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"off\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Leveraging NFV to become a pure software vendor</strong></h3>\r\nProcera Networks is a vendor of NFV equipment and Cam Cullen, VP, Global Marketing, explains the strategic underpinning of the industry shift from reliance on physical devices to full-blown Networks Functions Virtualisation. He also details the importance and benefits of working in close collaboration with Alcatel Lucent and the importance of its CloudBand NFV platform\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.telecomtv.com/embed/video/helping-service-providers-change-platforms-from-transport-to-innovation-12574/856/?autoplay=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"off\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Helping service providers change platforms: from transport to innovation</strong></h3>\r\nAlistair Scott, Director, CTO Office, JDSU explains that as the ripples caused by the global shift to cloud, network transformation and virtualisation continue to spread, companies are having to come to terms with a rapidly changing world - and that can be difficult. JDSU is also in long-term partnership with Alcatel-Lucent to provide world-beating virtualisation solutions for CSPs.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 last\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.telecomtv.com/embed/video/why-a-network-wide-cyber-defence-strategy-is-key-12496/821/?autoplay=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"off\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Enabling a network-wide cyber defense strategy with NFV</strong></h3>\r\nMichael O’Malley, VP Carrier Strategy &amp; BD, outlines Radware\'s SDN and NFV strategy for mobile carriers and service providers and emphasises the importance of applying an integrated security and application delivery framework that seamlessly enables comprehensive cyber defence and service delivery as network-wide native services. He also talks about the importance of Radware\'s ongoing collaboration with Alcatel Lucent and the many benefits it brings to both parties\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!--last-->\r\n<div class=\"clearboth\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/MfspeJrIqCI?showinfo=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Lightreading exclusive interview with Basil Alwan, President IP Routing &amp; Transport - Alcatel-Lucent</strong></h3>\r\