g></h3>\r\nThis interactive demonstration by the Cloud Innovation Center (CIC) shows the positive impact of agile service launch subject to Reliability, Availability, Serviceability (RAS) scenarios. It features an application centered system involving sophisticated Virtual Network Functions (VNF) and integrates Operations Support System (OSS), NFV’s Management and Orchestration (MANO) as well as Software Defined Networking (SDN) under a modular and scalable approach. In addition to Alcatel-Lucent’s portfolio, our conversation illustrates Ecosystem examples involving third party partners.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<!--</div>\r\nrow-->", "Videos", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "516-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-10-30 01:28:14", "2015-10-29 20:28:14", "", "516", "http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/516-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("979", "1", "2015-10-30 01:30:07", "2015-10-29 20:30:07", "<div class=\"row featured-video\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-2\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<h2>Featured Video</h2>\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/6JWyITbT8ec?showinfo=0\" width=\"720\" height=\"504\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3>NFV: moving from proof of concepts to commercial deployment</h3>\r\nNFV acceptance is progressing rapidly, with many proof of concepts and trials now completed, the focus is definitely shifting towards commercial deployments. A key success factor for NFV is the adoption of virtualization by Network Function Vendors who will play a key role in the transformation to NFV. This video is the highlight of interviews with four major network function vendors who share their view on NFV and their strategy in moving towards virtualization.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-2\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!--div class=\"row\"-->\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 col-sm-6 video\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/tTVeexoVU54?showinfo=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Alcatel-Lucent provides operators with the oxygen to innovate</strong></h3>\r\nThe goal with the new technologies, NFV and SDN, is to increase operational efficiency - that gives operators the oxygen to innovate. All the functions Alcatel-Lucent already has live in the network are on a virtualisation and cloudification journey. In this video, Bashkar Ghorti, highlights Alcatel-Lucent vision and strategy in enabling service provider to deploy NFV.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 col-sm-6 video\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Nq9eeW_-SmM?showinfo=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Using NFV to reach the services existing technology</strong></h3>\r\nPeter Margaris outlines the opportunities versus the challenges of NFV, as F5 sees them and, as a vendor of NFV equipment, explains how the virtualisation technology will particularly affect Layers 4 through 7 of the OSI model. He also lists the benefits of working in close collaboration with Alcatel-Lucent and just what Alcatel-Lucent\'s end-to-end and open NFV platform and ecosystem, CloudBand, brings to the party.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 col-sm-6 video\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/cA29TCfvd7Y?showinfo=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Leveraging NFV to become a pure software vendor</strong></h3>\r\nProcera Networks is a vendor of NFV equipment and Cam Cullen, VP, Global Marketing, explains the strategic underpinning of the industry shift from reliance on physical devices to full-blown Networks Functions Virtualisation. He also details the importance and benefits of working in close collaboration with Alcatel Lucent and the importance of its CloudBand NFV platform.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<!--</div>\r\nrow-->\r\n<div class=\"clearboth\"></div>\r\n<!--div class=\"row\"-->\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 col-sm-6 video\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/DMrd_xZmc0A?showinfo=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Helping service providers change platforms: from transport to innovation</strong></h3>\r\nAlistair Scott, Director, CTO Office, JDSU explains that as the ripples caused by the global shift to cloud, network transformation and virtualisation continue to spread, companies are having to come to terms with a rapidly changing world - and that can be difficult. JDSU is also in long-term partnership with Alcatel-Lucent to provide world-beating virtualisation solutions for CSPs.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 col-sm-6 video\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ug2MtqJDF-M?showinfo=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Enabling a network-wide cyber defence strategy with NFV</strong></h3>\r\nMichael O’Malley, VP Carrier Strategy &amp; BD, outlines Radware\'s SDN and NFV strategy for mobile carriers and service providers and emphasises the importance of applying an integrated security and application delivery framework that seamlessly enables comprehensive cyber defence and service delivery as network-wide native services. He also talks about the importance of Radware\'s ongoing collaboration with Alcatel Lucent and the many benefits it brings to both parties\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 col-sm-6 video\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/MfspeJrIqCI?showinfo=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Lightreading exclusive interview with Basil Alwan, President IP Routing &amp; Transport - Alcatel-Lucent</strong></h3>\r\nBasil Alwan, President of IP Routing &amp; Transport at Alcatel-Lucent, discusses virtualization, cultural challenges, the capex crunch and more with Light Reading founder and CEO Steve Saunders\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-2\"></div>\r\n<!--</div>row-->\r\n<!--div class=\"row\"-->\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 col-sm-6 video\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Y6VCgMkgDr4?showinfo=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Bringing NFV to production with CloudBand 3.0</strong></h3>\r\nRon Haberman, General Manager for Alcatel-Lucent CloudBand business unit, talks about what CloudBand 3.0 means for the Service Provider.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4 col-sm-6 video\">\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/bgcNRBl0nVQ?showinfo=0\" width=\"288\" height=\"160\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3><strong>Innovation and Lean Operations</strong></h3>\r\nThis interactive demonstration by the Cloud Innovation Center (CIC) shows the positive impact of agile service launch subject to Reliability, Availability, Serviceability (RAS) scenarios. It features an application centered system involving sophisticated Virtual Network Functions (VNF) and integrates Operations Support System (OSS), NFV’s Management and Orchestration (MANO) as well as Software Defined Networking (SDN) under a modular and scalable approach. In addition to Alcatel-Lucent’s portfolio, our conversation illustrates Ecosystem examples involving third party partners.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<!--</div>\r\nrow-->", "Videos", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "516-revision-v1", "", "", "2015-10-30 01:30:07", "2015-10-29 20:30:07", "", "516", "http://ecosystem.cloud-band.com/516-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
